			<ns0:name>bbu...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/106710594185928520364/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">While necessary, I don't think rotated text by itself would be sufficient. The plugin requires an entire 2-d graphics engine for high quality platform-specific rendering. This provides things like clip regions, drawing paths, line caps and joins, device-independent bitmap functions, and a bunch of other little things.

What's needed is a Pepper Graphics Engine. The PDF code contains these for Windows, Linux, and Mac, but of course we can't use it. Chrome contains something very similar for rendering HTML, which we could use.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-04-29T18:33:18.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-04-29T18:33:18.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 7 by bbu...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1694#c7" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1694/comments/full/7" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>